Sea levels rose at the end of the last glacial period and the transition into the current interglacial period as atmospheric CO2 levels rose by 90 ppm from 190 ppm to 280 ppm accompanied by rising northern hemisphere high latitude summer insolation (nhhlsi) and decreasing albedo as ice sheets retreated from large parts of high latitude North America and Europe, largely over a period of 3,000 to 4,000 years. 



